Pop your #kettle{} on to boil. Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into small pieces. Trim the @spring onion{1} and thinly slice. Halve the @red chilli{½} lengthways, deseed then finely chop. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped, stalks and all). Zest and halve the @lime{½}.

Heat a splash of @oil in a large #saucepan{} on medium heat. Add the pepper, garlic, chilli and half the spring onion. Stir and cook for ~{2%mins}, then add the @red Thai style paste{50} and stir together.

> TIP: Add less chilli if you don't like spice!

After ~{1%minute}, pour in the @coconut milk{200} and mix until smooth. Add the @chicken stock paste{10} with the @water{400} from your kettle (see ingredients for amount) and bring to a simmer.

Add the @peanut butter{30} and a pinch of @?sugar{pinch} to your pan. Simmer gently for ~{10%mins}. Taste the laksa and add seasoning if you think it needs it - @?salt{} @?pepper{} @?sugar{} - whatever suits your taste!

Meanwhile, heat a splash of @oil in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @diced chicken thigh{210} and lime zest. Season with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Stir-fry until cooked through, ~{8-10%mins}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling chicken and its packaging. The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

When cooked, remove to a #plate{} and cover with #foil{} to keep warm.

When the laksa has been cooking for ~{10%mins}, add in the @egg noodle nests{2} and @king prawns{150} to the sauce. Cook until the noodles are soft enough to eat and the prawns are cooked through, about ~{4%mins}.

> TIP: The noodles may soak up some of the coconutty liquid. If this is the case, just add a splash of water to get it back to a soupy consistency.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Add the chicken to the pan and simmer until the chicken is piping hot, ~{1-2%mins}. Remove from the heat and add half the lime juice. Taste and add salt, pepper and more lime juice if you feel it needs it. Serve in big #bowls{} topped with the coriander and the remaining spring onion. Enjoy!

> If you've opted to add prawns to your meal, add them to the sauce when you add the noodles and cook for the same amount of time. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands after handling raw prawns. The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.